# .governance-allowlist — TypeScript allowlist (estate "no new TypeScript" policy carve-outs).
# Mechanism: hyperpolymath/standards governance-reusable.yml -> check-ts-allowlist
# (Layer 2.5, "typed infrastructure file"). See docs/EXEMPTION-MECHANISMS.adoc.
#
# These are EXISTING TS-native infrastructure files, not new TypeScript:
#   * stack-orchestrator-mcp/adapter/*.ts — MCP cartridge adapter; the Model
#     Context Protocol SDK is TypeScript-native (mirrors boj-server's
#     MCP-adapter exemptions in its .claude/CLAUDE.md).
#   * proof-lsp/adapter/**/*.ts — Language Server adapter; the LSP server
#     tooling (vscode-languageserver) is TypeScript-native.
#   * tools/cartridge-minter/mint.ts — Deno scaffolding CLI.
#
# Unblock condition: migrate each to AffineScript once it has MCP / LSP /
# Deno-CLI bindings (tracked estate-wide with the boj-server adapter set).
#
# NB: the leading '*' absorbs the './' prefix the file-walker emits; the
# checker's glob '*' expands to '.*' (crosses '/'), so one line per adapter
# tree covers its nested files.
*cartridges/cross-cutting/orchestration/stack-orchestrator-mcp/adapter/*.ts
*cartridges/domains/formal-verification/proof-lsp/adapter/*.ts
*tools/cartridge-minter/mint.ts
